 mutation_18.txt        1  t      default  

--- wrong result 
Ubuntu :) select a,f from t where a =1;
af
 1  amute_1 


**Expected behavior**

The content of column f contains "mute_2" for a in range of [1, 45]

**Additional context**
From the code logic in StorageMergeTree::selectPartsToMutate(), we will break from the for loop  of mutations when max_ast_elements is exceeded, but for the future part, we assign the final mutation version to it. This is the root cause of missing update.

StorageMergeTree::selectPartsToMutate()
...
    size_t max_ast_elements = getContext()->getSettingsRef().max_expanded_ast_elements;
...
        size_t current_ast_elements = 0;
        for (auto it = mutations_begin_it; it != mutations_end_it; ++it)
        {
...

            if (current_ast_elements + commands_size >= max_ast_elements)
                break; >>>> Maybe we should save the last collected mutation, for this early break case?

            current_ast_elements += commands_size;
            commands.insert(commands.end(), it->second.commands.begin(), it->second.commands.end());
        }

        if (!commands.empty())
        {
            auto new_part_info = part->info;
            new_part_info.mutation = **current_mutations_by_version.rbegin()->first;** <<<< This is wrong when we break from above if
...

